        "t1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "enlarge_text": true,
            "text": "<p>Bumbu's artisans work in small batches, often carving each piece by hand from a single block of maple wood. Vitalie shapes the figures using techniques passed through a carpenter family for generations, while Marina hand-paints each piece with water-based natural paints. The tactile finishes and soft colors come from stains that highlight the grain rather than hide it, so every Bumbu toy carries the marks of the hands that made it.</p>"
