          "settings": {
            "title": "Stories Carved in Wood",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "t2": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "enlarge_text": true,
            "text": "<p>Bumbu Toys invite open-ended play in miniature worlds. Fairies tuck under mushroom caps. Forest animals gather around woodland scenes. Romanian folk-art knights, peasants, and historical figures bring the country's storytelling tradition into a child's play. Bumbu pairs beautifully with felt mats, silk play scarves, and other natural-materials toys for layered imaginative play.</p>"
          }
        },
        "h3": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why Families Choose My Toy Wagon for Bumbu Toys",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "t3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "enlarge_text": true,
            "text": "<p>We curate Bumbu because their commitment to handwork, maple wood, and non-toxic paints aligns with what we believe a toy should be: tactile, beautiful, and built to last. Every Bumbu order ships from our Los Angeles warehouse, with free shipping on orders $150 and over within the contiguous US. Returns are simple, and customer questions go to a real person on our team.</p>"
          }
        },
